Set the dashboard mode, currently has three modes: minimal, dual, full


Set Teleprompter Text (0x09)
??
Set Navigation Info (0x0A)
??
Set Head Up Angle Settings (0x0B)
Sets the angle at which the display turns on when the wearer looks up. Send to the right arm. Response is generic

Response

Set Display Settings (0x26)
Height and Depth
Control the display’s height and depth. Must be called twice, first with the preview bit set to 1, and then a few seconds later with the bit set 0. The glasses will stay on permanently until the preview=0 command is sent, or if the preview=1 is not sent, the glasses will reject the setting. The packet size of 08 seems to indicate it is a height+depth packet.

Response

Voice Activation on Head Lift Settings
Enables or Disables streaming audio to the phone when the head is lifted. A packet size of 06 seems to indicate the packet contains this setting instead of the height and depth settings.

Need to parse through the packets below:

